ns
	the inode pointing to the data of the root directory; as defined by the
	<code class=3D"constant">EXT2_ROOT_INO</code> constant.
  </p><p>
	In revision 0 directories could only be stored in a linked list.  Revision=
 1
	and later introduced indexed directories.  The indexed directory is backwa=
rd
	compatible with the linked list directory; this is achieved by inserting
	empty directory entry records to skip over the hash indexes.
  </p><div class=3D"sect1"><div class=3D"titlepage"><div><div><h2 class=3D"=
